aMule is a multiplatform ed2k client, fork of the eMule client, using
the wxWidgets class library. It was originally forked from the xMule
project, which in turn was forked from the lMule project. This is
turn was the first fork of eMule to run nativly on Linux and other
Unix-like systems.

libupnp is a optional dependency.

You can build optional features of aMule with following variables:

BUILD_DAEMON - amuled — headless daemon
BUILD_REMOTEGUI - amulegui — remote control GUI
BUILD_WEBSERVER - amuleweb — HTTP web interface
BUILD_AMULECMD - amulecmd — CLI client for the daemon
BUILD_ED2K - ed2k — eD2k link handler helper
BUILD_ALC - alc — aMuleLinkCreator GUI
BUILD_ALCC - alcc — aMuleLinkCreator console
BUILD_CAS - cas — C statistics tool (Unix only)
BUILD_WXCAS - wxcas — GUI statistics tool
BUILD_FILEVIEW - fileview — console file viewer (experimental)
BUILD_TESTING - Unit test suite
ENABLE_NLS - Native-language support (gettext)
ENABLE_UPNP - UPnP port forwarding
ENABLE_IP2COUNTRY - IP→country mapping (libmaxminddb)
ENABLE_MMAP - Use memory-mapped file I/O where supported
